meshExamples: [
	{
		id:       "ex-conservation-invariant-pbt"
		scenario: "Developer implements antecipação calculation: valor_liquido = valor_face - deságio - taxa_plataforma. Manual tests pass with R$1.000 at 2.5% taxa and 0.5% plataforma fee. QA approves. In production: operation for R$33,33 with taxa 3.333% produces valor_liquido = R$32,21 but deságio + taxa = R$1,11 + R$0,02 = R$1,13. R$33,33 - R$1,13 = R$32,20 ≠ R$32,21. R$0,01 discrepancy. Over 10.000 operations/month: R$100/month of unaccounted centavos."
		analysis: "Root cause: rounding applied to each component independently. deságio rounds to R$1,11. taxa rounds to R$0,02. Sum of rounded components: R$1,13. valor_face - sum = R$32,20. But valor_liquido was calculated by rounding (valor_face × (1-taxa-plataforma)) directly = R$32,21. Two different rounding paths produce different results. Manual tests: R$1.000 doesn't trigger this (clean division). R$33,33 with fractional taxa: triggers."
		recommendation: "(1) Property-based test that would have caught this: property('conservation') { forAll(genOperation()) { op -> val sum = op.valor_liquido + op.deságio + op.taxa assertEquals(op.valor_face, sum, 'conservation violated: face=${op.valor_face} sum=${sum}') } }. With generator producing R$33,33 at 3.333%: property violated. PBT shrinks to minimal failing case. (2) Fix: single rounding path. Calculate deságio = round(valor_face × taxa_rate). taxa = round(valor_face × plataforma_rate). valor_liquido = valor_face - deságio - taxa. Valor_liquido is derived (not independently rounded). Conservation holds by construction. (3) Alternative: 'last component absorbs remainder.' deságio = round(valor_face × taxa_rate). taxa = round(valor_face × plataforma_rate). valor_liquido = valor_face - deságio - taxa. This always conserves (valor_liquido is whatever remains). (4) Add to edge case catalog: EC-017: 'fractional taxa rate producing different results via independent vs sequential rounding.' Test: {valor: 3333, taxa: 3.333%, plataforma: 0.50%}. Expected: conservation holds. (5) Add property to CI: runs 10.000 iterations on every build. Catches this class of bug for any amount × rate combination. (6) CLAUDE.md: 'monetary calculations: NEVER round intermediate results independently. Calculate components sequentially with last-component-absorbs-remainder pattern. Property test: conservation invariant must pass.'"
